><td align="left">82</td><td char="." align="char">2.761</td><td char="." align="char">3.044</td><td char="." align="char">0.002331</td></tr><tr><td align="left">1</td><td align="left">rs580233</td><td align="left">12486792</td><td align="left">A</td><td align="left">ADD</td><td align="left">82</td><td char="." align="char">16.31</td><td char="." align="char">2.621</td><td char="." align="char">0.008777</td></tr><tr><td align="left">1</td><td align="left">rs9430736</td><td align="left">12600010</td><td align="left">A</td><td align="left">ADD</td><td align="left">82</td><td char="." align="char">2.413</td><td char="." align="char">2.673</td><td char="." align="char">0.007509</td></tr><tr><td align="left">1</td><td align="left">rs6684199</td><td align="left">13880522</td><td align="left">G</td><td align="left">ADD</td><td align="left">82</td><td char="." align="char">3.628</td><td char="." align="char">2.743</td><td char="." align="char">0.006089</td></tr><tr><td align="left">1</td><td align="left">rs34482377</td><td align="left">18216603</td><td align="left">C</td><td align="left">ADD</td><td align="left">82</td><td char="." align="char">0.3639</td><td char="." align="char">− 2.616</td><td char="." align="char">0.008885</td></tr></tbody></table><table-wrap-foot><p>(A) Clinical file for input in CLIN_SKAT by users. G<italic>i</italic> and Age<italic>i</italic> are gender and age, respectively for i<sup>th</sup> individual (Indiv <italic>i</italic>). The variables Indiv <italic>i</italic>, G<italic>i</italic> and Age<italic>i</italic> have been used for the purpose of deidentiying the participants in the Brugada Syndrome dataset. (B) Genotype File format (PLINK binary format) for input in CLIN_SKAT by users, (C) Merged input file created by CLIN_SKAT for running <bold><italic>functional_analysis</italic></bold>, (D) Output of the function <bold><italic>functional_analysis</italic></bold>, chromosome number (CHR), rsID (SNP), physical position (BP), minor allele (A1), g